pullRequest.title: Update to SDK 0.12.0
pullRequest.bodyText:
Now that @jkwatson fixed the horrible bug where OpenTelemetry instances were not actually behaving as instances, I think our instrumentation approach of only instrumenting key global methods stopped working. I think we could instead instrument every single global static (which often have default methods implemented at the non-global level) but instead tried a different approach of implementing an ApplicationOpenTelemetry.
Also after some drift, this is checking ObfuscatedTracerProvider in the SDK, not the Obfuscated in the API
https://github.com/open-telemetry/opentelemetry-java/blob/master/sdk/all/src/main/java/io/opentelemetry/sdk/OpenTelemetrySdk.java#L51
While it could be changed to check for that API internal Obfuscated class, I figured we may as well just instrument the SDK with the agent instead of forcing that internal-sdk-agent dependency.
